                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/11–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-19T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 19, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 20—11:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>703. In acknowledging today receipt of Mr. Stainov’s note, text of which
                    transmitted mytel 700, November 17, 1 conveyed to MinFonAff <pb facs="0402"
                        n="390" xml:id="pg_390"/> contents Department’s tel 375, November 17<note
                        n="14" xml:id="d397fn1">See footnote 12, <ref target="#pg_386">p.
                        386</ref>.</note> to make sure that accurate report of what was said to
                    General Stoichev by Under Secretary of State reaches Bulgarian authorities.</p>
                <p>I am repeating this to Moscow as 319 and suggest that Department repeat its 375
                    also.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
